
Solsys Azure EventHub Consumer for Splunk
=========================================

Copyright (C) 2019 - 2020 Solsys Inc.  All rights reserved

* **Add-on Homepage:** Linux:    https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/5025
                       Windows:  TBD
* **Authors:** Darren Fuller, Duncan Summerville, Dindu Paul - Solsys


### Description ###

The Eventhub Consumer is a modular input that brings data in from an Azure EventHub and indexes it into Splunk


### Installation ###

To install, decompress the app into the $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps directory on a v8+ heavy forwarder machine and restart Splunk.

To monitor an EventHub, go to Settings -> Data inputs -> Azure Eventhub Consumer and fill out the form.   
You require the Eventhub Namespace, eventhub name, SAS Policy name, and SAS Policy Key 

Additional props and transforms may be required to format the data coming in and for mapping data to the Splunk Common Information Model.  Please contact Solsys for assistance on this.


### Binary File Declaration ###

This app contains the following compiled binary files: 

- Part of the Python CFFI Library used by the cryptology library, allowing python to run C code
bin/_cffi_backend.cpython-37m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so

- Part of the cryptology library used to communicate to the eventhub
bin/cryptography/hazmat/bindings/_padding.abi3.so
bin/cryptography/hazmat/bindings/_openssl.abi3.so
bin/cryptography/hazmat/bindings/_constant_time.abi3.so


